title: Magnetic fishing set
body:
Introduce your little one to the joy of fishing with this engaging Magnetic Fishing Set — a fun and educational toy that turns playtime into a learning adventure! Perfect for toddlers and young children, this colorful set includes a variety of magnetic sea creatures and sturdy fishing rods designed for little hands.

🧲 Strong Magnets
Each fish features a securely embedded magnet that connects easily with the fishing rods, helping kids build coordination and patience.

🎨 Bright, Kid-Friendly Design
With vibrant colors and playful shapes, the set sparks imagination and keeps children entertained for hours.

🧠 Educational Benefits
Improves fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination, color recognition, and even basic counting or sorting.

🌊 Safe & Durable Materials
Crafted from non-toxic wood or plastic (depending on the version), with smooth edges and child-safe paint for worry-free play.

What’s Included:

  • 🎣 2 magnetic fishing rods

  • 🐠 8 Assorted magnetic fish and sea creatures

title: Sands Alive kinetic sand set
body:
Unleash creativity and tactile exploration with the Sands Alive™ Kinetic Sand Kit! This engaging sensory play set includes premium kinetic sand, a handy spoon, and three adorable animal figures to spark imaginative play.

🌟 What’s Inside?

  • Soft, moldable kinetic sand that never dries out and sticks only to itself

  • One easy-to-handle spoon for scooping, shaping, and digging

  • Three cute animal figures to create stories, scenes, and adventures

🎨 Endless Creativity
Perfect for building castles, digging tunnels, or just feeling the unique texture that’s both calming and entertaining.

🧠 Sensory & Development Benefits
Encourages fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination, and imaginative thinking while providing soothing sensory input.

🛡️ Safe & Non-Toxic
Made from kid-safe materials, free from harmful chemicals, and easy to clean up.

What’s Included:

  • 1 tray, 1 spoon, 1 roller and kinetic sand

  • Comes with 3 molds (1 mold is half missing)

title: Tap Tap art
body:
Tap Tap Art Hammer & Nails Set – Creative Building Fun for Kids!

Let your little builder’s imagination soar with the Tap Tap Art Hammer and Nails Set — a safe, colorful, and hands-on toy that combines creativity with fine motor skill development.

🔨 What’s Inside?

  • Kid-sized wooden hammer designed for easy gripping

  • Colorful wooden nails and shapes to hammer into a sturdy base

  • A smooth wooden board to create endless patterns and pictures

🎯 Benefits:

  • Boosts hand-eye coordination and concentration

  • Encourages creativity and problem-solving

  • Develops strength and dexterity through active play

🛡️ Safe & Durable:
Made from high-quality, non-toxic wood with smooth edges, perfect for little hands.

title: Peg board
body:
Miniland Pegs – Colorful Fun for Little Hands!

Encourage creativity, fine motor skills, and pattern recognition with Miniland Pegs, a vibrant set of chunky, easy-to-handle pegs perfect for preschoolers and toddlers.

🧩 Features:

  • Brightly colored, large pegs designed for small hands

  • Durable and safe, made from non-toxic materials

  • Compatible with Miniland pegboards and other creative playsets

🎨 Educational Benefits:

  • Develops hand-eye coordination and dexterity

  • Sparks imagination through sorting, counting, and pattern-making

  • Enhances color recognition and early math skills

title: Bedtime for little bears

"Little Bear flumped down in the snow and wiggled his tail. 'I'm not sleepy,' he said, 'and I don't want to go to bed yet.' "Mother Bear smiled. 'Shall we take one last walk,' she said, 'and see who else is going to bed?'" Little Bear and Mother Bear take one last walk to see the other animals getting ready for bed. Will this make Little Bear sleepy enough to snuggle down for the night? With cuddly illustrations painted in cool tones, this wonderful bedtime book is the perfect story for any child who isn't quite ready to go to sleep.

title: The Park in the Dark
body:
A hugely endearing picture book from the makers of the Big Bear and Little Bear series. When the sun goes down and the moon comes up, the toy monkey and his friends, Loopy the elephant and Little Gee the dog, creep softly out of the bedroom, down the stairs and through the dark hall on their way to the deserted park. The park's an exciting place to be after dark, though a little bit scary - especially when the Thing (a night train) hurtles out of the darkness, seeming to chase them. Then the three friends run all the way home and jump back into bed, safe and sound once more. Now a classic story, The Park in the Dark won the 1989 Kurt Maschler Award and has now been reissued to appeal to a new generation of young children.

title: Puddle's Big Step
body:
'When Puddle was barely more than an egg, he couldn't wait to start duckling school.' So begins this story about feelings of excitement, anticipation, and understandable nervousness that surround an approaching first day at nursery school. Puddle, a little duckling, is like so many pre-school children in desperately wanting to be grown-up enough to go to school and to have his own school bag. But as the day draws nearer, Puddle begins to feel rather wobbly about the whole concept! Luckily Mummy knows just what to do. She packs items into Puddle's school bag that will help him through his first day - one of her softest feathers to remind him she is never far away, some home-made biscuits for him to share with his new friends, his Cuddly for the afternoon nap - and, as the story unfolds, we discover how Puddle's enjoyment of his first day builds each time he finds one of Mummy's tokens in his bag. Puddle spends a happy day counting caterpillars, matching ladybirds, leaping from lily pad to lily pad, and decorating a leafy twig. So, by going-home time, he can put his twig in his bag to take home for Mummy.
